    "created_at": "2018-12-17T13:03:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-12-17T13:03:16Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There are three chunk sizes that could be considered \"special\":\r\n\r\n* aligned with hash function block size - this helps make good use of the hash function itself in terms of entropy and avoiding arbitrary padding\r\n* aligned with hash output size - this would help make all nodes in the tree have the same size, after chunking\r\n* aligned with the largest `tree_hash_root` output - all inputs have to pass through this function, so using the same here makes it easier to avoid arbitrary-length buffers in the tree hashing code",
